underway. Train yards can communicate with trains by radio. If the trains are within
about 20 miles of the yard, the entire communication path is wireless. However, longerrange
communications use landlines to repeater stations along the train routes. The
repeater station batteries provide only about 24 hours of standby power.
Shipment of critical supplies likely could resume under manual control operations.
Transporting food from farms to storage warehouses and from storage warehouses to cities
