interoperability switch.11 The testing was performed with the equipment in stored, dormant,
and operating states. No failures were experienced at test levels up to 50 kV/m. The
interoperability switch was also tested up to 50 kV/m with no adverse effects.
Based on these results, the interoperability switch capability is expected to function
normally after an EMP attack. However, the computer network link between the interoperability
switch and the dispatch station may fail at field levels as low at 3 to 6 kV/m.
This would necessitate manual operation of the switch to implement the connections
among various law enforcement, fire, and EMS agencies.
